{
  "_comment": "RUNTIME STATE (the durable spine, half 1 of 2). Lives at <repo>/.goalkeeper/plan.json and holds ONLY loop runtime: status, passing, attempts, iteration, prevGoodHead, and fpHistory. The durable WORKING CONTRACT (goal, items, replanCount, critiqueRounds) now lives in a SEPARATE file, contract.json, beside this one; the bookkeeper writes plan.json every round and never touches contract.json. The init step reads BOTH at the start of a run. A fresh `goalkeeper` invocation does NOT start over: it loads this file and resumes by restoring `passing`, `attempts`, `prevGoodHead`, `iteration`, and `fpHistory` (all of these round-trip). From those, the 3-retry, no-progress, and oscillation guards are rebuilt exactly where the last run left off. The script merges these fields verbatim, so keep the keys exactly as named.",
